      • addOtuNode

        public void addOtuNode(OtuNode node)
                throws Exception
        Description copied from interface: ParserModule
        Each sample with taxonomic assignments from a ClassifierModule is parsed by ParserModule.parseSamples() to produce a ParsedSample. As each file is processed, this method is called to add the OtuNode to the ParsedSample with the same sample ID (if valid).
        Specified by:
        addOtuNode in interface ParserModule
        Overrides:
        addOtuNode in class ParserModuleImpl
        Parameters:
        node - OtuNode
        Throws:
        Exception - if unable to add the OTU node

      • parseSamples

        public void parseSamples()
                  throws Exception
        Parse all KrakenClassifier reports in the input directory.
        Cache the leaf counts Build an KrakenNode for each line.
        If ParserModuleImpl.isValid(OtuNode),
        1. Create ParsedSample for the OtuNodeImpl.getSampleId() if not yet created.
        2. Add the OtuNodeImpl.getCount() (1) to ParsedSample OTU count.

        Sample Kraken report line (head 7A_reported.tsv) :
        FCC6MMAACXX:8:1101:1968:2100#GTATTCTC/1 d__Bacteria|p__Bacteroidetes|c__Bacteroidia|o__Bacteroidales|f__Bacteroidaceae|g__Bacteroides|s__Bacteroides_vulgatus

        Specified by:
        parseSamples in interface ParserModule
        Specified by:
        parseSamples in class ParserModuleImpl
        Throws:
        Exception - if error occurs while parsing classifier reports

      • getCitationString

        public String getCitationString()
        Description copied from interface: ApiModule
        At a minimum, this should return the name and/or url for the wrapped tool. For BioLockJ home-grown modules, it can cite BioLockJ and give the current version. Ideally this will include the version for the wrapped tool. Tool version may require using a stored variable that can be filled in during execution; and the string that is returned pre-execution may not have the version.
        Specified by:
        getCitationString in interface ApiModule
